The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                              NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	New Delhi, Jan. 2 (PTI): Sonia Gandhi, in hospital for a chest infection, is making steady progress but has been advised rest.          
	She had a comfortable night and slept well. Her progress is steady and she is responding well to treatment, said B.K. Rao, the chairman of the board of management of Sir Gangaram Hospital, where she was admitted on New Years Day. However, party spokesperson Jayanthi Natarajan said Sonia was likely to be discharged in a day or two.                  
	 Bangalore (PTI): The alleged woman serial killer recently arrested here for murdering six women is suspected to have killed three more. Police are planning to conduct a narco-analysis test on Mallika, 43, as she failed to give a satisfactory reply on her activities between 1999 to 2007, the period in which she is suspected to have committed the murders.                  
	New Delhi (PTI): The Centre had no answer on Wednesday to Delhi High Courts query over whether a group of ministers is reviewing the metro project connecting central and south Delhi. The court asked the Centre to inform it about the status of the GOM on Thursday.                  
	Moga (PTI): Unidentified armed persons with muffled faces looted the shop of a Bengali jewellary manufacturer on Tuesday night at the Ramganj area here. Brandishing firearms and sharp-edged weapons, they allegedly robbed gold ornaments worth about Rs 1 lakh at gun point from Mohan Jewellers.                  
	Nagpur (PTI): A police sub-inspector allegedly committed suicide here on Wednesday. Vinod Bhosale, 30, shot himself with his service revolver at his rented residence. The reason behind the suicide is not yet known.                  
	 Jammu (PTI): A youth impersonating as a policeman was arrested on Wednesday. Subhas Chowdhary used to extort money from shopkeepers at a bus stand here.                                                                                                                           
